      "raw_text": "NORTH YAKIMA, Jan. o.\nWhile teaching school at Yakima\nCity few years ago, Charles N.\nStahl, now resident of Brawley,\nCal, saved up couple of hundred\ndollars and bought 100 acres of\ndry\" land near Mabton from a\nhomesteader, who had decided that\nthe land was worthless. Yester-\nday Mr.. Stahl sold the quarter Sec\nton to Alex Miller of North Yak\nina for $4,000, a profit of $15,S. %\non his original investment. The\nbuilding of the Mabton siphon by\nthe reclamation service makes the\nland irrigable and of value."
    }
